# Session 14 Handover — Fumage

## What was done this session

### New article — Beyond the Counter (`/guide/niche-fragrance-houses`)
Eleven niche house profiles in a single article: Creed, Amouage, Parfums de Marly, Xerjoff, Initio Parfums Privés, Nishane, Nasomatto, D.S. & Durga, Tauer Perfumes, Roja Parfums, and Maison Margiela Replica. Each card includes house origin and descriptor, editorial body, and `FragLinks` picking verified database IDs. Occasion context grid (four scenarios) and a niche vs. bespoke comparison table. Registered in `GuideIndex.tsx` under "Niche · Houses". Commit `1659437`.

### New article — The Smart Shelf (`/guide/smart-shelf`)
Seven Gulf/value-tier house profiles: Armaf, Lattafa, Afnan, Rasasi, Al Haramain, Maison Alhambra, Ard Al Zaafaran. Includes the clone economy explainer, Gulf fragrance tradition context, a four-tier wardrobe framework (Pinnacle / Niche Core / Gateway / Smart Shelf), and a seven-row niche-to-value pairing table with linked fragrance references. Registered under "Buying Guide · Value". Commit `420a824`.

### New article — Where a Fragrance Comes From Changes Everything (`/guide/regional-traditions`)
The largest article yet: eight regional traditions (French, Italian, Mediterranean, English, Oriental, Arabian, American, Japanese), each with motto, editorial body, signature notes pills, a 6-card fragrance grid (linked where slugs exist), and a "when to reach for" wear note. Three inline editorial callouts (concentration primer, French vs. Italian philosophy, Arabian value proposition). At-a-glance comparison table (8 rows × 5 columns), four budget tier cards, two starter wardrobes (Value ~$250–350; Without Compromise ~$900–1,200), and a footnote section on German and Nordic traditions. 48 fragrance references total; 20 link to catalog pages. Registered under "Education · Regional". Commit `dcd625d`.

